Unemployment Analysis with Python
Project Overview

Unemployment is one of the most important economic indicators that reflects the health of a country's economy. The COVID-19 pandemic significantly disrupted economic activities across India, resulting in job losses and increased unemployment rates. This project analyzes unemployment trends in India using Python and investigates the impact of COVID-19 on employment opportunities.

The dataset contains monthly unemployment statistics for various states and union territories in India, including unemployment rate, employment estimates, labor participation rate, and area classification (Urban/Rural). The analysis focuses on identifying trends, comparing state-wise unemployment rates, understanding the effects of the pandemic, and deriving meaningful insights that can support policy decisions.

Dataset Information

Dataset Name: Unemployment in India

Source: Kaggle

Features
Feature	Description
Region	State or Union Territory
Date	Date of observation
Frequency	Monthly
Estimated Unemployment Rate (%)	Percentage of unemployed people
Estimated Employed	Number of employed individuals
Estimated Labour Participation Rate (%)	Percentage of population participating in labor force
Area	Urban or Rural
